1
00:00:05,275 --> 00:00:08,538
Kriget i Europa fortsätter genom en serie av rådgivande känslor.

2
00:00:08,598 --> 00:00:14,740
Efter den största invasningen av Europa, förberedde allmänheten i väst den stupendösa kriget på Holand.

3
00:00:14,801 --> 00:00:19,463
Den starkaste armén som kunde flytta på luft var att bygga upp i Britannien.

4
00:00:20,004 --> 00:00:22,024
Paratrooper och glidertrooper.

5
00:00:22,045 --> 00:00:25,126
Den här aktionen var också en av de bäst hållbara sekreterna i kriget.

6
00:00:25,146 --> 00:00:28,628
Den visade sig till invandrarna i Holand när det var för tidigt att göra dem något bra.

7
00:00:29,292 --> 00:00:32,914
Den här ljuset tippade en annan skala mot de germanska armén i Europa.

8
00:00:33,316 --> 00:00:36,999
Den geniösa av allierade militära strategi uppstår en annan masterström.

9
00:02:32,408 --> 00:02:33,348
Nu på grunden.

10
00:02:33,908 --> 00:02:35,770
En annan fjäll öppnas upp till allierade arm.

11
00:02:36,250 --> 00:02:39,050
Nya tröjor utvecklas på den norska och belgiska grunden.

12
00:02:39,091 --> 00:02:43,633
Armerna av de vänsterdemokraterna släpper in på den kraft som försöker rulla världen med kraft.

13
00:02:43,652 --> 00:02:57,236
Våra soldater mötte unga norska som också kämpade för tyskarna.

14
00:03:02,664 --> 00:03:04,385
De allierade arméerna har tagit Maastricht.

15
00:03:05,046 --> 00:03:08,188
Detta namn minskar den ominösa kriget av den germanska armén i maj 1940.

16
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:12,372
När vi förväntade oss att flöden i Holmland skulle återkomma för att hålla kriget tillbaka.

17
00:03:12,872 --> 00:03:21,120
Men ingen sån lucka var vår portion i 1940.

18
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:25,683
Detta är bombningen av Boulogne, sedan tagit av Royal Air Force Bomber Command.

19
00:03:25,704 --> 00:03:30,567
Den germanska high command-strategin förlorade sin briljantis när krigsforskningen förlorade initiativet i kriget.

20
00:03:31,542 --> 00:03:37,963
Men utifrån konfusionen har Wehrmacht försökt att hänga på till de tillgängliga porten i Holland, Belgien och Frankrike.

21
00:03:37,984 --> 00:03:53,188
Men en på en, de porten faller till våra armar.

22
00:03:53,229 --> 00:03:58,411
Och nu, för alla som har soffit i handen av tyskarna och Tyskland, det här är det du väntat dig i fem långa år.

23
00:03:59,804 --> 00:04:02,165
Allied Soldiers enter Hitler's Germany.

24
00:04:02,186 --> 00:04:23,259
This is one more place where the railway was bombed before the Germans pulled out.

25
00:04:23,298 --> 00:04:26,560
It is a Belgian border town annexed by Germany in her days of victory.

26
00:04:31,074 --> 00:04:33,055
Inhabitanten här är germanska.

27
00:04:33,076 --> 00:04:37,057
Det finns ingen väg av blås och smil som vägen till Paris och Brussel.

28
00:04:37,077 --> 00:04:41,180
Vi måste förstå att de här människorna har varit nöjda med att bli regerade av Hitler och hans nazister.

29
00:04:41,220 --> 00:04:45,281
Nöjda med att se honom plunga världen i smärta i sin bidrag till att regera världen.

30
00:04:45,862 --> 00:04:47,983
De har inte försökt att rädda sig av Hitler.

31
00:04:51,084 --> 00:04:53,526
Det här är Rötgen, den första staden i Tyskland.

32
00:05:04,071 --> 00:05:08,673
Inside the German frontier the camera brings us to the first fortifications of the Siegfried Line.

33
00:05:11,814 --> 00:05:15,216
One pillbox bears a notice saying that Hitler has personally inspected it.

34
00:05:15,555 --> 00:05:17,437
His intuition told him not to stop in it.

35
00:05:18,877 --> 00:05:20,778
Nearby is the German town of Wallendorf.

36
00:05:20,838 --> 00:05:24,860
When American troops entered Wallendorf they saw white surrender flags on every building.

37
00:05:24,879 --> 00:05:28,062
Then suddenly shots were fired and some of the American soldiers fell.

38
00:05:28,766 --> 00:05:31,288
The Americans therefore burned Wallendorf to the ground.

39
00:05:31,747 --> 00:05:34,230
This is the kind of language that Germans understand.

40
00:05:37,192 --> 00:05:47,240
The story of a small American patrol which accepted the surrender of a German general and 20,000 of his men with all their weapons supplies our conclusion to this edition of Go More British News.

41
00:05:48,411 --> 00:05:53,473
Lieutenant McGill var beredd att förlora sig och han gick in i de germanska linjerna för att hitta ut vad det var om.

42
00:05:53,492 --> 00:05:57,355
Av alla de fantastiska historierna av den här fantastiska kriget, den här är högst rankad.

43
00:05:57,595 --> 00:06:00,055
Om den hade varit berättad, så trodde du inte på det.

44
00:06:00,437 --> 00:06:00,937
Men här är den.

45
00:06:01,541 --> 00:06:09,244
Reproduced by the war correspondents movie camera as it took its place in war history.

46
00:06:09,264 --> 00:06:10,403
General Eric Elster.

47
00:06:11,124 --> 00:06:14,165
He and his men have been making their way towards Germany from the south of France.

48
00:06:14,665 --> 00:06:16,004
Harassed by the Mackie.

49
00:06:16,105 --> 00:06:18,565
They decided to seek out an American unit and surrender.

50
00:06:18,985 --> 00:06:22,105
The size of the unit they found was approximately only a score.

51
00:06:22,706 --> 00:06:28,288
And the amazing scene of formal surrender through an interpreter to an American general is now recorded.

52
00:06:34,798 --> 00:06:40,142
General Alster, has surrendered the units remaining with him because with the means in his hands, he had not the ability to break through to the German frontier.

53
00:06:40,202 --> 00:06:44,766
Accordingly, he surrendered his command, these marching groups, the foot troops, and the service elements to the United States Army.

54
00:06:44,786 --> 00:06:45,247
General Alster,

55
00:07:05,384 --> 00:07:10,769
Acting for the commanding general of the 9th United States Army, Lieutenant General William H. Simpson, and on behalf of the Army of the United States, I accept your surrender.

56
00:07:10,788 --> 00:07:13,630
You, your officers and men will be given treatment in accordance with the principles of the Geneva Convention.

57
00:07:39,504 --> 00:07:46,107
They were allowed to approach with their arms and ammunition because they said they feared the vengeance of the Mackie if they left themselves defenseless on the way.

58
00:07:46,127 --> 00:07:56,391
They're losing the war.

59
00:07:56,571 --> 00:07:57,831
They've had enough of it.

60
00:07:58,291 --> 00:08:00,892
And so they surrender and get out of it.

61
00:08:00,913 --> 00:08:05,915
No such easy course lay open to the millions of innocent men and women who didn't want a war when the Germans started it.

62
00:08:06,430 --> 00:08:08,634
They had to live through five years of fury.

63
00:08:09,194 --> 00:08:11,617
Countless thousands of innocent people had to die in agony.

64
00:08:12,358 --> 00:08:17,144
But Europe's bullies have had enough of their war until next time they feel they're strong enough to win.

65
00:08:17,944 --> 00:08:23,872
Even amid the satisfaction we feel in these days of our victory we must ask ourselves what they may do in the future.

66
00:08:24,692 --> 00:08:26,776
And remember what they have done in the past.
